A:

There are many ways to achieve this.  The easiest is to create a custom directive.  Something like:
angular.module('myModule', []).directive('myDirective', function () {
    return {
        restrict: 'A',
        link: function (scope, element, attrs) {
            scope.myValue = 'foo';
        }
    };
});

You can then use it in your html with something like:
<my-directive my-value="myValue"></my-directive>

See the Plunker here.

Disease and treatment-related mortality in a large cohort of allogeneic hematopoietic stem cell transplantation recipients.
The aim of this study was to analyze the disease and treatment-related mortality (DRM) in allogeneic hematopoietic stem cell transplantation (HSCT) recipients. In a prospective cohort of allogeneic HSCT recipients, DRM was defined as death attributable to underlying malignancy, infection, or other causes. The main cause of death was disease (TRD, 26.0 %), followed by infection (26.1 %). The cumulative incidence of DRM was 23.7 % (95 % CI 22.2-25.1). The most common underlying malignancies were hematological cancer (44.9 %), followed by non-hematological malignancies (25.1 %). The cumulative incidence of DRM was 19.0 % (95 % CI 17.5-20.5). In multivariable analysis, age at the time of HSCT (HR 1.03 [95 % CI 1.01-1.04]; P = 0.002), lower lymphocyte count at the time of HSCT (HR 1.01 [95 % CI 1.00-1.02]; P = 0.008), and the presence of a second malignancy (HR 1.19 [95 % CI 1.01-1.40]; P = 0.038) were associated with an increased risk of DRM. The cumulative incidence of mortality was 9.9 % (95 % CI 8.9-11.0) in the first year after transplantation, but was decreased to 4.5 % (95 % CI 4.3-4.8) at 5 years and to 1.5 % (95 % CI 1.4-1.6) after 10 years. The presence of a second malignancy was associated with a decreased risk of mortality. HS

